2\int_0^a \int_0^{\pi \over 2} {r \over 1 + r^2\cos^2(\theta)}\,d\theta\,dr
= 2\int_0^a r \int_0^{\pi\over 2} {\sec^2(\theta) \over \sec^2(\theta) + r^2}\,d\theta\,dr
= 2\int_0^a r \int_0^{\pi\over 2} {\sec^2(\theta) \over \tan^2(\theta) + (1 + r^2)}\,d\theta\,dr
= 2\int_0^a r \int_0^{\infty} {1 \over u^2 + (1 + r^2)}\,du\,dr
= 2\pi\int_0^a r {1 \over \sqrt{1 + r^2}}\,dr
=\pi \sqrt{1 + r^2}\,\,\,\bigg|_{r = 0}^{r = a}
=\pi\sqrt{1 + a^2} - \pi
